    java.io.Serializable
    public class SongFile
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    This class is a value object design pattern This class hold the required attributes for every song. It has setter and getter methods to set and get the value. The object can also be created using the constructor with all the values to be set are passed as parameters This class implements Serializable interface to convert the conversion of a Java object into a static stream (sequence) of bytes, which we can then save to a database or transfer over a network
